ston \n|-\n|'''3:49.4'''|| || [[John Walker (runner)|John Walker]] || {{NZL}} || 12 August 1975<ref name=iaaf/>|| Gothenburg\n|-\n|'''3:49.0'''|| 3:48.95 || [[Sebastian Coe]] || {{GBR}} || 17 July 1979<ref name=iaaf/>|| Oslo \n|-\n|'''3:48.8'''|| || [[Steve Ovett]] || {{GBR}} || 1 July 1980<ref name=iaaf/>|| Oslo \n|-\n|'''3:48.53'''|| || [[Sebastian Coe]] || {{GBR}} || 19 August 1981<ref name=iaaf/>|| Z\u00fcrich \n|-\n|'''3:48.40'''|| || [[Steve Ovett]] || {{GBR}} || 26 August 1981<ref name=iaaf/>|| Koblenz \n|-\n|'''3:47.33'''|| || [[Sebastian Coe]] || {{GBR}} || 28 August 1981<ref name=iaaf/>|| Brussels\n|-\n|'''3:46.32'''|| || [[Steve Cram]] || {{GBR}} || 27 July 1985<ref name=iaaf/>|| Oslo \n|-\n|'''3:44.39'''|| || [[Noureddine Morceli]] || {{ALG}} || 5 September 1993<ref name=iaaf/>|| Rieti \n|-\n|'''3:43.13'''|| || [[Hicham El Guerrouj]] || {{MAR}} || 7 July 1999<ref name=iaaf/>|| Rome\n|}\n\nThe \"Time\" column indicates the ratified mark; the \"Auto\" column indicates a fully automatic time that was also recorded in the event when hand-timed marks were used for official records, or which was the basis for the official mark, rounded to the 10th of a second, depending on the rules then in place. \n\nRecords for the mile were rounded up to the nearest tenth of a second commencing January 1, 1957. Previously, records were rounded up to the nearest fifth of a second. Those rounded-up marks were: Cunningham's 4:06.8 (timed at 4:06.7); H\u00e4gg's 4:06.2 (4:06.1); H\u00e4gg's 4:01.4 (4:01.3); Landy's 3:58.0 (3:57.9). Landy's mark was not retroactively adjusted when the new rule came into effect.<ref name=\"wrp\">{{cite web |url=http://iaaf-ebooks.s3.amazonaws.com/2015/Progression-of-IAAF-World-Records-2015/projet/IAAF-WRPB-2015.pdf |title=IAAF World Records Progression |edition=2015 |author1=Hymans, Richard |author2=Matrahazi, Imre |publisher=[[International Association of Athletics Federations]] |format=pdf |accessdate=November 6, 2017}}</ref>{{rp|vii; 69\u201370}} Auto times to the hundredth of a second were accepted by the IAAF for events up to and including 10,000 m beginning in 1981.<ref name=iaaf/>\n\n==Men's Indoor==\n\n===Men Indoor Pre-IAAF===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Time !!Auto !!Athlete !!Nationality !!Date !!Venue\n|-\n|'''4:39.2'''|| || [[Lawrence Myers]] || {{USA}} ||  April 25, 1885 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:39.2'''|| || [[Ernest Hjertberg]] || {{USA}} || May 10, 1889 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}} \n|-\n|'''4:31.4'''|| || [[William Day (athlete)|William Day]] || {{USA}} ||  February 5, 1890 || [[Brooklyn]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:28.4'''|| || [[Ernest Hjertberg]] || {{USA}} ||  February 13, 1892 || [[Boston]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:26.0'''|| || [[Andrew Walsh (athlete)|Andrew Walsh]] || {{USA}} ||  November 30, 1895 || [[Brooklyn]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:25.2'''|| || [[Melvin Sheppard]] || {{USA}} ||  January 26, 1906 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:23.8'''|| || [[Melvin Sheppard]] || {{USA}} ||  March 30, 1906 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:19.8'''|| || [[Herbert Trube]] || {{USA}} ||  February 13, 1909 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:19.8'''|| || [[Oscar Hedlund]] || {{USA}} ||  February 22, 1912 || [[Troy]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:18.8'''|| || [[Oscar Hedlund]] || {{USA}} ||  February 12, 1913 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:18.2'''|| || [[Abel Kiviat]] || {{USA}} ||  February 15, 1913 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:16.0'''|| || [[John W. Overton|John Overton]] || {{USA}} ||  March 10, 1917 || [[Philadelphia]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:14.6'''|| || [[Joie Ray (athlete)|Joseph Ray]] || {{USA}} || April 12, 1919 || [[Chicago]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:13.6'''|| || [[Paavo Nurmi]] || {{FIN}} ||  January 6, 1925 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:13.4'''|| || [[Lloyd Hahn]] || {{USA}} ||  February 14, 1925 || [[New York City|New York]] {{USA}}\n|-\n|'''4:12.0'''|| || [[Paavo Nurmi]] || {{FIN}} ||  March 7